### Component 2: CNC Data Simulator (Replaces Layers 1+2)

#### [NEW] [data_simulator/simulator.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/data_simulator/simulator.py)
Generates synthetic CNC time-series data with realistic machine behavior:

- **Normal baseline**: vibration ~0.3-0.5g, temperature ~35-45В°C, current ~1.5-2.0A
- **Fault injection modes**:
  - `bearing_wear`: gradual vibration increase + spikes
  - `spindle_imbalance`: periodic high-frequency vibration bursts
  - `overheating`: temperature ramp beyond threshold
  - `overload`: sudden current spikes + temperature rise
- **Output**: CSV dataset with `timestamp, vibration, temperature, current, machine_state, fault_type`
- Generates 50,000+ rows covering ~14 hours at 1-second intervals
- Mix: ~70% normal, ~30% fault patterns distributed across types

#### [NEW] [data_simulator/stream_to_api.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/data_simulator/stream_to_api.py)
Reads generated CSV and streams rows to the FastAPI ingestion endpoint via HTTP POST, simulating real-time ESP32 data transmission at configurable rate.

