### Component 3: Data Ingestion API вЂ” Layer 3

#### [NEW] [api/main.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/api/main.py)
FastAPI application entry point. Mounts all routers, CORS middleware, startup/shutdown events (DB init).

#### [NEW] [api/routers/ingest.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/api/routers/ingest.py)
- `POST /api/v1/ingest` вЂ” receives single sensor JSON payload, validates, stores raw
- `POST /api/v1/ingest/batch` вЂ” batch ingestion endpoint
- `GET /api/v1/ingest/latest` вЂ” latest N raw readings

#### [NEW] [api/routers/analytics.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/api/routers/analytics.py)
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/sensor/{sensor_name}` вЂ” historical sensor data with time range
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/summary` вЂ” statistical summary
- `GET /api/v1/analytics/correlation` вЂ” cross-sensor correlation

#### [NEW] [api/routers/anomaly.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/api/routers/anomaly.py)
- `GET /api/v1/anomaly/latest` вЂ” latest anomaly result
- `GET /api/v1/anomaly/history` вЂ” anomaly history with time range

#### [NEW] [api/routers/health.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/api/routers/health.py)
- `GET /api/v1/health/current` вЂ” current health score + risk level
- `GET /api/v1/health/history` вЂ” health score history

#### [NEW] [api/routers/labels.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/api/routers/labels.py)
- `POST /api/v1/labels` вЂ” submit fault label for a time range
- `GET /api/v1/labels` вЂ” list all labels
- `GET /api/v1/labels/count` вЂ” count labeled events (used for phase transition)

#### [NEW] [api/routers/alerts.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/api/routers/alerts.py)
- `GET /api/v1/alerts` вЂ” list alerts with filters
- `PUT /api/v1/alerts/{id}/acknowledge` вЂ” acknowledge an alert

#### [NEW] [api/routers/ml.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/api/routers/ml.py)
- `GET /api/v1/ml/status` вЂ” current ML phase, model metrics
- `POST /api/v1/ml/retrain` вЂ” trigger model retraining
- `GET /api/v1/ml/predictions` вЂ” latest predictions

#### [NEW] [api/schemas.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/api/schemas.py)
Pydantic models: `SensorReading`, `AnomalyResult`, `HealthScore`, `FaultLabel`, `Alert`, `MLStatus`, etc.

