### Component 4: Preprocessing & Feature Engineering вЂ” Layer 4

#### [NEW] [services/preprocessing.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/services/preprocessing.py)
- Moving average smoothing (window=10)
- IQR-based outlier capping
- Min-Max normalization
- Feature extraction:
  - `rms_vibration` вЂ” root mean square over rolling window
  - `temp_gradient` вЂ” rate of temperature change (В°C/min)
  - `current_variance` вЂ” variance over rolling window
  - `vibration_peak_ratio` вЂ” peak/mean ratio
  - `rolling_mean`, `rolling_std` for each sensor
- Returns structured feature vector per timestamp

---

### Component 5: Time-Series Storage вЂ” Layer 5

#### [NEW] [database/db.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/database/db.py)
SQLite database manager: connection pool, table creation, WAL mode.

#### [NEW] [database/models.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/database/models.py)
6 tables as per Backend Design Document:
1. `raw_sensor_data` вЂ” timestamp, vibration, temperature, current
2. `processed_features` вЂ” all extracted features per timestamp
3. `anomaly_results` вЂ” anomaly_score, is_anomaly, model_type
4. `health_scores` вЂ” health_score, risk_level, timestamp
5. `fault_labels` вЂ” operator-submitted labels with fault_type
6. `alerts` вЂ” alert_type, severity, message, acknowledged

#### [NEW] [database/crud.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/database/crud.py)
CRUD operations for all 6 tables: insert, query by time range, get latest N, aggregations.

---

### Component 6: ML Intelligence Engine вЂ” Layer 6

#### [NEW] [ml/engine.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/ml/engine.py)
Main ML orchestrator: decides current phase (A/B/C), runs appropriate model(s), returns predictions.

#### [NEW] [ml/isolation_forest.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/ml/isolation_forest.py)
Phase A: Unsupervised anomaly detection using sklearn `IsolationForest`.
- Train on feature vectors from normal operation
- Output: anomaly_score (-1 to 1), is_anomaly flag
- Persistence: save/load via joblib

#### [NEW] [ml/classifier.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/ml/classifier.py)
Phase B/C: Supervised classification using XGBoost.
- Train on labeled feature vectors
- Output: fault_type probability distribution, predicted class
- Classes: `normal`, `bearing_wear`, `spindle_imbalance`, `overheating`, `overload`

#### [NEW] [ml/trainer.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/ml/trainer.py)
Retraining pipeline: fetch labeled data, train models, evaluate, persist if improved.

---

### Component 7: Health Score & Risk Engine вЂ” Layer 7

#### [NEW] [services/health_engine.py](file:///c:/Users/Keerthi Sridhar/Desktop/GAURDX/services/health_engine.py)
- `Health = 100 - (w1 * anomaly_risk + w2 * temp_risk + w3 * vibration_risk + w4 * current_risk)`
- Default weights: anomaly=0.4, vibration=0.25, temperature=0.2, current=0.15
- Rolling average smoothing (window=10)
- Persistence validation: anomaly must persist 5+ consecutive readings
- Risk classification: Healthy (80-100), Warning (60-80), Critical (40-60), High Risk (<40)

